www.jamaicaobserver.com/Entertainment/New-album-from-Kartel_57846 New album from Kartel] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160421090604/http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/entertainment/New-album-from-Kartel_57846 |date=21 April 2016 }}\", ''[[Jamaica Observer]]'', 15 April 2016. Retrieved 23 April 2016</ref>\n* Label: Adidjahiem Records/TJ Records/Zojak World Wide\n* Format: CD, digital\n|align=center|2\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|''To Tanesha'' <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.dancehallmag.com/2020/01/10/music/vybz-kartels-new-album-to-tanesha-is-out-now.html|title=Vybz Kartel\u2019s New Album \u2018To Tanesha\u2019 Is Out Now|last=McLeod|first=Sheri-kae|publisher=DancehallMag|date=January 10, 2020|accessdate=January 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|\n* Released: 10 January 2020\n* Label: Short Boss Musik/Vybz Kartel Muzik\n* Format: Digital\n|align=center|- \n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"\u2013\" indicates album did not chart or was not released in the country\n|}\n\n===Extended plays===\n* 2009: ''GAZA''\n* 2010: ''Raw - EP''\n* 2011: ''The Gaza Don''\n* 2011: ''Colouring Book''\n* 2012: ''Stronger We Get''\n* 2012: ''Amsterdam''\n* 2012: ''Mentally Free''\n* 2013: ''Time To Be Free''\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|US R&B]]\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Tekk Buddy\"\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2004\n| align=center| 111<ref>Peaked at #11 on the Bubbling Under R&B/Hip-Hop Songs chart, a chart of 25 spots below the 100-spot Hot R&B/Hip-Hop chart. [http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=is_bmdb_track_id%3A408724&f%5B1%5D=itm_field_chart_id%3A345&refine=1 Source]</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''More Up 2 Di Time''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Picture This\"\n| align=center| 121<ref>Peaked at #21 on the Bubbling Under R&B/Hip-Hop Songs chart, a chart of 25 spots below the 100-spot Hot R&B/Hip-Hop chart. [http://www.billboard.com/biz/search/charts?f%5B0%5D=is_bmdb_track_id%3A400411&f%5B1%5D=itm_field_chart_id%3A345&refine=1 Source]</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Ramping Shop\" <small>(featuring [[Spice (singer)|Spice]])</small>\n|rowspan=\"4\"| 2009\n| align=center|76<ref>{{BillboardURLbyName|artist=vybz kartel|chart=all}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"4\"|''Pon di Gaza 2.0''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Life Sweet\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Go Fi Dem Anyweh\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Last Man Standing\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Clarks Again\"\n| rowspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n|align=center|\u2013\n|rowspan=\"8\"|Single only\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Know Bout Me\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Like Xmas\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"All Out\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"8\"|2011\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Step Up Inna Life\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Tell You Say\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Sex & the City\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Slew Dem Like David\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Go Go Wine\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''Kingston Story''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Yuh Love\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Summertime\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|Colouring Book\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Party Me Say (Me Nice)\"\n| rowspan=\"13\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|2012\n| align=center| \u2013\n| rowspan=\"3\"|''Mentally Free''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Reparation\" <small>(featuring Gaza Slim)</small>\n| align=center| \u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Street Vybz Girl\"\n| align=center| \u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" | \"Good Father\"/\"Mi Sorry\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n| rowspan=8|Single only\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Right Now\" <small>(featuring Stylish)</small>\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Dweet We a Dweet (Do It)\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Lip Gloss (Cover Girl)\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"The Cure (Fi Badmind)\" <small>(featuring Rvssian)</small>\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Looking Glass\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Party Vibes\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Informer\" <small>(featuring Tommy Lee)</small>\n|align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Betray Di Gaza Boss\" <small>(featuring Tommy Lee)</small>\n|align=center|\u2013\n|''Unstoppable''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Daddy Devil\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n|''Gaza Man Crazy EP''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Love U Baby\"\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"9\"|2013\n| align=center|\u2013\n|''Unstoppable''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Back to Life\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n| rowspan=\"7\"|''Kartel Forever Trilogy''\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Look Pon We\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Ghetto Life\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Summer Time\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Bubble Hard\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Me A Pree\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Dancehall Hero\"\n| align=center|\u2013\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"|\"Badman Sittin\"\n|align=center|\u2013\n| Single only\n|-\n|\"Fever\"\n|2016\n|align=center|\u2013\n|King of the Dancehall\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"font-size:90%\" | \"\u2014\" denotes a title that did not chart, or was not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n====As featured artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:8em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"2\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Reggae Digital Songs|US Reggae Digital]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width: